Indian Equities: Kernex Microsystems, Punj Lloyd, Rolta India

-- B y   H e m a l   S a v a i
-- 
2011-10-05T11:54:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/indian-equities-kernex-microsystems-punj-lloyd-rolta-india.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Indian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3:30 p.m. close in Mumbai.  The BSE India Sensitive Index, or Sensex, fell 0.5 percent
to 15,792.41. The BSE200 Index dropped 0.5 percent to 1,950.39.  Kernex Microsystems India Ltd. (KMSI)   rose 2.1 percent
to 90.5 rupees, the biggest gain in a month. The software maker
got an order worth 167.7 million rupees from Konkan Railway.  Punj Lloyd Ltd. (PUNJ)   gained 1.1 percent to 52.95
rupees, the largest gain in a week. Qatar Solar Technologies, a
unit of the  Qatar Foundation , said yesterday it awarded an
engineering, procurement and construction contract to Punj Lloyd
Group.  Rolta India Ltd. (RLTA)   dropped 9.2 percent to 70.3
rupees, its lowest since Apr. 2, 2009. The maker of design
software’s founder pledged 4.6 percent of co.’s equity.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hemal Savai in Mumbai at  at
 hsavai@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 